ActCanada Wildlife Act
SubjectDesignation of Regulatory Provisions for Purposes of Enforcement (Canada Wildlife Act) Regulations
PrecisDESIGNATION OF REGULATORY PROVISIONS FOR PURPOSES OF ENFORCEMENT (CANADA WILDLIFE ACT) REGULATIONS in order to complete the fine regime introduced by the Environmental Enforcement Act by designating offences in regulations under the Canada Wildlife Act that are subject to the regime of minimum fines and higher maximal fines, in order to ensure that fines reflect the seriousness of designated offences.
